      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make dough and chill, 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Melt {{unsalted-butter}}, {{soft-brown-sugar}}, and {{golden-syrup}} together in a small saucepan until the sugar dissolves. Remove from the heat and leave to cool for 5 minutes. Combine {{plain-flour}}, {{ginger-ground}}, {{cinnamon-ground}}, and {{bicarbonate-of-soda}} in a large bowl. Pour in the melted mixture and add the {{eggs}}. Mix to a smooth dough. Wrap and chill for 30 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll, cut, and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 190°C (170°C fan). Roll the dough on a lightly floured surface to about 5 mm thick. Cut out figures or shapes and place on lined baking trays, leaving 2 cm between them. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until set and slightly darker at the edges. They will firm as they cool, so pull them while the centres still look slightly underdone. Transfer to a wire rack. Decorate once completely cool.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
